1
00:00:00,083 --> 00:00:02,043
Do you want to make a bet?

2
00:00:02,293 --> 00:00:04,462
If you pass, you buy the drinks.

3
00:00:04,462 --> 00:00:06,006
If you fail, I'll buy.

4
00:00:06,506 --> 00:00:08,550
I buy the drinks?

5
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:10,343
Don't want to?

6
00:00:10,343 --> 00:00:10,927
If not...

7
00:00:10,969 --> 00:00:12,012
No.

8
00:00:12,887 --> 00:00:13,638
I'd love to.

9
00:00:15,515 --> 00:00:16,599
Make sure you pass.

10
00:00:16,599 --> 00:00:18,143
If you don't want a free drink from me.

11
00:00:18,935 --> 00:00:20,020
Okay.

12
00:00:22,647 --> 00:00:25,483
Finally spoke to him.

13
00:00:25,483 --> 00:00:28,570
But is this okay?

14
00:00:28,570 --> 00:00:32,490
I don't have much time left here anyway.

15
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:51,384
(Text: Application Rejected)

16
00:00:51,634 --> 00:00:53,595
Rejected again.

17
00:00:54,888 --> 00:00:56,306
Why...

18
00:00:57,140 --> 00:01:00,685
Why did I fail!

19
00:01:04,647 --> 00:01:07,108
Mr. Laundry.

20
00:01:07,317 --> 00:01:10,779
You said I would pass.

21
00:01:10,779 --> 00:01:14,824
You said I was lucky.

22
00:01:14,824 --> 00:01:17,035
But I failed...

23
00:01:27,170 --> 00:01:31,591
Mr. Laundry...

24
00:01:31,591 --> 00:01:34,511
I failed.

25
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:50,693
Huh?

26
00:01:51,402 --> 00:01:52,779
Mr. Laundry.

27
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:54,781
I came to get a free drink,

28
00:01:54,781 --> 00:01:56,825
but it looks like I'll have to buy.

29
00:01:57,909 --> 00:02:00,328
Hyung, you said I would pass.

30
00:02:00,995 --> 00:02:04,749
I really thought I would pass this time.

31
00:02:04,749 --> 00:02:07,043
I even kept my shirt collar stiff.

32
00:02:08,378 --> 00:02:11,089
You're calling me Hyung naturally now.

33
00:02:11,089 --> 00:02:12,841
You're really drunk.

34
00:02:12,841 --> 00:02:14,092
Drink some water.

35
00:02:14,551 --> 00:02:15,510
You'll ruin your stomach.

36
00:02:21,015 --> 00:02:23,393
Do you know what I thought today?

37
00:02:24,477 --> 00:02:26,688
What did you think?

38
00:02:28,898 --> 00:02:31,442
I feel like a stretched-out T-shirt.

39
00:02:31,693 --> 00:02:32,819
Pardon?

40
00:02:33,695 --> 00:02:37,824
Other applicants were wearing nice clothes,

41
00:02:38,449 --> 00:02:42,203
but I looked so shabby.

42
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:49,294
I only have this one worn-out shirt, just like me.

43
00:02:49,294 --> 00:02:51,254
The interviewers looked at me,

44
00:02:51,462 --> 00:02:53,256
and I felt so ashamed of being shabby.

45
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:58,928
I couldn't even answer their questions.

46
00:03:06,811 --> 00:03:09,355
Just keeping the collar stiff isn't enough.

47
00:03:10,940 --> 00:03:13,818
No matter how much you iron a stretched T-shirt,

48
00:03:13,818 --> 00:03:16,070
it doesn't become new.

49
00:03:25,246 --> 00:03:26,706
So,

50
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:29,834
did you leave without saying anything?

51
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:33,379
I did say something.

52
00:03:33,379 --> 00:03:35,882
"I'm slower than others.

53
00:03:35,882 --> 00:03:38,301
But I never miss what I've seen once.

54
00:03:38,301 --> 00:03:42,805
I work hard!" That's what I said.

55
00:03:44,140 --> 00:03:45,266
But,

56
00:03:46,768 --> 00:03:49,729
who likes someone who just works hard these days?

57
00:03:49,729 --> 00:03:52,315
Who would hire a slow person?

58
00:03:53,399 --> 00:03:55,860
Everyone is busy running,

59
00:03:55,860 --> 00:03:58,696
looking for people who are good.

60
00:04:00,949 --> 00:04:02,825
I'm screwed.

61
00:04:04,535 --> 00:04:05,703
Even if you were the interviewer, Hyung,

62
00:04:05,703 --> 00:04:08,164
you wouldn't have hired someone like me, right?

63
00:04:09,832 --> 00:04:13,169
Who would like such a pathetic person?

64
00:04:15,421 --> 00:04:17,090
You're not pathetic at all.

65
00:04:22,095 --> 00:04:24,013
I envy you.

66
00:04:24,555 --> 00:04:27,892
Why would you envy a failed life?

67
00:04:29,936 --> 00:04:31,729
I ran without brakes for 10 years,

68
00:04:31,729 --> 00:04:33,398
and then I broke down.

69
00:04:34,565 --> 00:04:37,235
I should have admitted I was slow,

70
00:04:37,235 --> 00:04:39,612
but I couldn't and kept running,

71
00:04:39,612 --> 00:04:43,241
until I couldn't stop anymore.

72
00:04:43,241 --> 00:04:44,617
That's why I envy you.

73
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:48,579
You know how to acknowledge yourself.

74
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:52,041
That takes quite a bit of courage.

75
00:04:58,923 --> 00:05:00,967
So don't say you're pathetic.

76
00:05:06,973 --> 00:05:08,725
You're not wrong.

77
00:05:08,725 --> 00:05:11,227
You're just different from others.

78
00:05:11,227 --> 00:05:15,231
You have better strengths that others don't have.

79
00:05:15,231 --> 00:05:17,400
Being more prudent than others,

80
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:19,027
and knowing how to acknowledge yourself

81
00:05:19,027 --> 00:05:20,903
is really amazing.

82
00:05:22,488 --> 00:05:24,073
Thanks for saying that.

83
00:05:27,827 --> 00:05:29,370
I mean it.

84
00:05:29,954 --> 00:05:31,581
But,

85
00:05:34,375 --> 00:05:36,669
are you always this sweet to everyone, Hyung?

86
00:05:38,921 --> 00:05:41,466
Saying nice things,

87
00:05:42,592 --> 00:05:46,804
and being handsome... if you do that...

88
00:05:51,934 --> 00:05:53,895
If I do that?

89
00:06:02,487 --> 00:06:04,572
Stop charming people.

90
00:06:06,866 --> 00:06:08,826
You think you'll fall for me if I talk?

91
00:06:09,577 --> 00:06:10,536
Yes.

92
00:06:12,121 --> 00:06:14,916
Do you like my face?

93
00:06:16,793 --> 00:06:17,585
Yes.

94
00:06:19,045 --> 00:06:22,131
What do you want to do to me?

95
00:06:22,131 --> 00:06:23,299
Do what you want.

96
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:27,595
What are you imagining?

97
00:06:33,559 --> 00:06:34,894
We definitely ki...

98
00:06:35,937 --> 00:06:36,979
Ki?

99
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:40,817
Ki... kissed...

100
00:06:42,777 --> 00:06:44,570
I must be crazy.

101
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:46,197
What was I imagining!

102
00:06:46,989 --> 00:06:48,032
I think I'm drunk.

103
00:06:48,032 --> 00:06:50,326
I'll go first.

104
00:07:11,431 --> 00:07:12,348
Wait up.

105
00:07:20,815 --> 00:07:22,108
You seem drunk,

106
00:07:22,775 --> 00:07:24,610
so I'm holding you so you don't fall.

107
00:07:26,487 --> 00:07:29,240
I can't pretend not to notice anymore.

108
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:31,659
Even though I know I shouldn't,

109
00:07:31,659 --> 00:07:34,412
I keep wanting to get closer to you.

110
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:35,663
Hyung!

111
00:07:38,249 --> 00:07:39,292
Let's go.

112
00:07:39,292 --> 00:07:41,043
I'll walk you home.
